abstract: House Committee receives documents requested from FBI related to investigation into Hillary Clinton's private email server; Republicans contend documents could prove Clinton committed perjury when she testified she did not send or receive classified emails; Clinton's campaign expresses concern Republicans could leak selective details to both discredit her and publicly undermine FBI’s decision not to recommend criminal charges against Clinton.

headline.print_headline: F.B.I. Provides Congress Email Inquiry Documents
headline.main: F.B.I. Gives Congress Documents Related to Hillary Clinton E-Mail Inquiry

keywords.value: House Committee on Oversight and Government Reform
keywords.name: organizations
